    {
      "id": "1f655170ef6e3ef34d3eef792532c1bc0209eb75",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 177,
        "name": "John Hammond",
        "email": "jhammond@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "jhammond"
      },
      "date": "2017-12-08 15:33:17.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> The main confusion that reviewers have is that e.g. llite calls obd_get_info(), but they don't know that it goes to lov_get_info() or lmv_get_info() depending on which export is used. I think it would be better to keep the EXP_CHECK_MD_OP() and friends macros, but remove these obd_*() functions and OBP() and have llite call lov_get_info() or lmv_get_info() directly as needed.\n\nFor llite calling lov and lmv operations this is maybe OK. But in general we would lose the ability to write generic code that calls obd_get_info(). Code in lustre/obdclass/ uses the obd_*() wrappers.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
